surface: Dull dolden colour; v. small traces of v. dk brown sur.
description: Dimensions: L 394mm; Wbl 61.0; Wm 29.3; min B flanges by openings 7.2; openings 10 x 47; 10 x 48.5; Ds 265 (?+); wt,Typology: Loz. section midrib gives way to circular socket around blade base; blade at mouldings are stepped in profile; very acute profile rim round openings; s. mouth [?survinley] flattened.,Manufacture: cg. flash visible only inside lunate openings - off centre on socket sides both towards same face.,Condition: edges intact and sharp; v. slight bend at tip in profile; simple hole perforates socket wall close to mouth; tiny cracks at mouth; ?punched dent in midrib at bl. base.,Attached material: Good length of shaft present - broken end visible has peg impression, this end is very oval in section (hence depth s. measurement goes way beyond).
